Here's how to implement all three requirements:

## 1. Custom "Cancel" back button on `EditProductPage`

```xml
<!-- EditProductPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage ...>
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <!-- rest of your page -->
</ContentPage>
```

## 2. ViewModel with confirmation logic

```csharp
public partial class EditProductViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    bool hasUnsavedChanges;

    [RelayCommand]
    async Task Back()
    {
        if (hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!discard) return;
        }
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

## 3. Guard the hardware/swipe back gesture in `AppShell`

The custom button handles taps, but users can also swipe back or press the hardware back button. Guard that in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the default back arrow with a "Cancel" label and routes taps through your ViewModel.
- `OnNavigating` with `GetDeferral()` intercepts swipe/hardware back — the deferral is required because `DisplayAlert` is async.
- Check `args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so you only guard backward navigation, not forward pushes.
